Added optional revspec parameter to git-delorean (defaults to HEAD).

git-delorean can now accept a revspec argument to specify which commit to
find parents for. If not provided, defaults to HEAD.

Usage examples:
- git delorean (analyzes HEAD)
- git delorean my-branch (analyzes my-branch)
- git delorean abc123 (analyzes specific commit)

Makes the script more flexible for analyzing different commit histories.

/Claude-haiku@4.5

Improved readability of git-delorean xargs invocation.

Split the xargs command arguments across multiple lines with proper indentation
for better readability in git-delorean's git commit --fixup invocation.

This is a style-only change that makes the pipeline easier to follow.

/Claude-haiku@4.5
